<div class="dog-card-show">
  <div class="card-img-show", style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0),rgba(0,0,0,0.7)), url('<%= cl_image_path(@dog.photo.key)%>')">
    <div class="match-buttons">
      <%= link_to matches_path(authenticity_token: form_authenticity_token, match: { matching_dog_id: current_user.dogs.first, matched_dog_id: @dog.id, status: Match::STATUS[2]}), class: "r-match" do %>
        <i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i>
      <% end %>
      <%= link_to matches_path(authenticity_token: form_authenticity_token, match: { matching_dog_id: current_user.dogs.first, matched_dog_id: @dog.id, status: Match::STATUS[0]}), class: "a-match" do %>
        <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="card-description-show">
    <div class="basic-dog-info">
      <h2><%= @dog.name %></h2>
      <h5>Address: <%= @dog.address %></h5>
      <h5>Breed: <%= @dog.breed %></h5>
      <h5>Age: <%= @dog.age[:year] %> years and <%= @dog.age[:month] %> months</h5>
      <h5>Pedigree: <%= @dog.pedigree %></h5>
      <h5>Gender: <%= @dog.gender %></h5>

    </div>
    <div class="dog-description">
      <p>Dogs are generally much better at conserving heat than at cooling themselves.
     In sled dogs, who can survive outdoors even in bitterly cold temperatures, the fur acts as an insulating “blanket” that retains the heat generated by the dog’s high metabolism.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
